Understanding your **true investment return** requires accounting for both capital growth and income, and adjusting for inflation. The ASX 200 has delivered approximately **9.5–10.5% total annual returns** (including dividends) over the past 20–30 years before inflation, or approximately 6.5–7.5% in real terms.

Enter your initial investment, final value, holding period, and annual distributions to calculate total return, CAGR (compound annual growth rate), and real (inflation-adjusted) CAGR. Use CAGR to compare investments of different holding periods on an apples-to-apples basis.
